title: Library Contract Request: Gale General OneFile

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Oregon Public Records Law, I hereby request the following records:

The most recent contract, governing, base, or master license agreement with Gale relating to the licensing of Gale's General OneFile;
1)  All related terms and conditions, terms of service, amendments, addenda, appendices, attachments, product terms, MOUs, MOAs, data processing agreements, and/or letters of intent; and
2)  All financial documents or records of financial transactions, exchanges or obligations related to the contractual relations with Gale for database licensing.

Please do not limit your search to strictly direct agreements or renewals between the State Library of Oregon and the vendor (Gale), but include all agreements and related documentation that provide access to this licensed material for Authorized Users affiliated with Central Oregon Community College.

Responsive materials include all contracts, agreements, amendments, appendices, invoices, and any other documents listed above that incorporate language governing terms of use of Gale’s General OneFile.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 business days.

Sincerely,

Ellen Dubinsky

communications.subject: California Public Records Act Request: UCSF PRA Databases
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1 — any databases and/or spreadsheets used to track requests under the California Public Records Act from January 1, 2024 to the date of this request's fulfillment.
2 — any and all policy documents, manuals, memos and/or reports regarding the processing of public records requests from January 1, 2024 to the date of this request's fulfillment.

In the regard to the database requested in paragraph 1, please provide the database in its original electronic format pursuant to Cal. Gov. Code § 6253.9.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ed Burton

communications.subject: Illinois Freedom of Information Act. Request: Property Inventory Metadata
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Dear FOIA Officer,

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act, 5 ILCS 140, I request access to and copies of the following records:

Metadata from the property inventory system underlying the property seizure/forfeiture Form 4-64, including the following fields for all property inventoried between January 1, 2001 and the present:

Recovered date
RD number
Inventory number
ID number
Description of property
Inventory type
IUCR code
State charges
Beat of recovery
Status (e.g., hold for investigation, property available for return to owner, to be disposed of, etc.)
Statute
Statute description
Whether or not the property is in CPD possession
I request that the responsive records be provided in CSV or Excel format if available, or another machine-readable format.

If you determine that portions of the requested records are exempt from disclosure under FOIA, please provide the non-exempt portions and cite the specific statutory exemption(s) justifying the redaction or withholding.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Filed Requests
